The paper proposes a novel framework for FAQ-based question answering that utilizes knowledge graphs. The paper focuses on natural language processing and information retrieval, which are the main topics of the cs.CL (Computation and Language) sub-category. The use of knowledge graphs also suggests a connection to the cs.IR (Information Retrieval) sub-category. Additionally, the paper utilizes machine learning techniques, which are relevant to the cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) sub-category. The multi-channel matching strategy and query-document matching task also suggest a connection to the cs.LG (Machine Learning) sub-category. Finally, the paper involves the construction and use of knowledge graphs, which is relevant to the cs.DB (Databases) sub-category.
